eft is a pale pink incontinence pad labeled “Poise.” On the right is a similar pad labeled with the TENA logo and “InstaDRY.” The TENA side also includes the green flower graphic in the corner. The pads are displayed flat and upright, side by side, as a visual comparison.\n\nBack in the white demonstration room, the woman stands behind the table, now with a large board behind her showing several portrait photos of different women and a visible TENA product package with purple labeling. The portraits show smiling women of varying appearances, arranged in a grid-like layout, while the presenter remains centered in front.\n\nThe action returns outdoors to cycling. The woman is now riding a bike on a leafy, sunlit road, wearing a white cycling helmet, dark wraparound sunglasses, the light blue cycling jersey, and dark spandex cycling shorts. Another cyclist rides slightly behind her. She pedals with a focused, active posture, leaning forward over the handlebars. Close views show her lower body and the white bicycle: her hands grip the bars, her black saddle and a small red rear reflector are visible, and her legs move through the pedaling motion in fitted black shorts.\n\nThe woman’s face returns close up against the pale backdrop, again without the helmet and sunglasses, speaking directly to the viewer with a confident, friendly expression. Then the coastal road scene reappears: she stands centered on the white backdrop with her white bicycle, while cyclists continue to pass along the winding road behind and in front of her. The golden hills and ocean remain visible around the artificial white display area.\n\nNear the end, the white backdrop brightens and visually transforms into a clean product display on a white background. A rectangular TENA InstaDry package appears upright, decorated with the lime-green flower graphic near the top. The TENA InstaDry branding is visible to the left and on the package, and a phone number appears in large blue text below: “1-877-GET-